 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","title":"[audit][types] Strengthen cancelled reasons in Outcome::join and fix ok_or_else contract","description":"Audit follow-up from batch asupersync-1qfd0.332 for src/types/outcome.rs. Concrete defects: (1) Outcome::join/join_outcomes are left-biased even when both sides are Cancelled, so weaker reasons like user cancellation can beat stronger reasons like shutdown and lose cleanup-priority metadata; align with CancelReason::strengthen and combinator join semantics. (2) Outcome::ok_or_else docs currently claim preserved non-Ok distinctions, but the implementation erases Err/Cancelled/Panicked into a single fallback error; fix the contract in the same file while touching the surface. Scope: update implementation/docs/tests in src/types/outcome.rs only, with focused regression coverage and rch-backed validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259514038Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:57:32.259490525Z","close_reason":"Patched src/types/outcome.rs so Cancelled+Cancelled joins strengthen to the worse CancelReason, corrected ok_or_else docs to reflect collapsing behavior, and validated with focused rch-backed tests plus cargo check; package clippy remains blocked only by unrelated existing issues in src/plan/fixtures.rs and src/transport/aggregator.rs, and cargo fmt --check is blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/transport/aggregator.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:52:32.251304229Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","title":"[audit][http] Preserve identity default preference when Accept-Encoding only sets wildcard quality","description":"Audit follow-up in src/http/compress.rs. negotiate_encoding() currently applies wildcard quality to identity before the special-case default from RFC 9110 section 12.5.3. That makes headers like '*;q=0.5' incorrectly lower identity to q=0.5 and potentially prefer a compressed encoding, even though an unencoded representation is acceptable by default unless explicitly excluded by identity;q=0 or *;q=0 without a more specific identity entry. Scope: fix identity negotiation semantics and add focused regression tests in src/http/compress.rs only, validating with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","title":"[audit][http] Preserve identity default preference when Accept-Encoding only sets wildcard quality","description":"Audit follow-up in src/http/compress.rs. negotiate_encoding() currently applies wildcard quality to identity before the special-case default from RFC 9110 section 12.5.3. That makes headers like '*;q=0.5' incorrectly lower identity to q=0.5 and potentially prefer a compressed encoding, even though an unencoded representation is acceptable by default unless explicitly excluded by identity;q=0 or *;q=0 without a more specific identity entry. Scope: fix identity negotiation semantics and add focused regression tests in src/http/compress.rs only, validating with rch-backed targeted tests/checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:06:28.576659325Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.332","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:01:34.508319147Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.333","title":"[audit][web] Make ErrorHandlerMiddleware negotiate ordinary 4xx/5xx responses","description":"src/web/negotiate.rs documents ErrorHandlerMiddleware as rewriting both panics and ordinary error responses according to the client's Accept header, but the implementation only catches panics and returns existing 4xx/5xx responses unchanged. That breaks the middleware's advertised content-negotiation contract and leaves handler-produced errors in inconsistent formats. Scope: preserve non-content headers, rewrite 4xx/5xx bodies/content-type through the existing formatter, add focused regressions for negotiated client/server errors, and keep panic handling intact.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonPeak","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:04:55.006704120Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:21:32.170571556Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:21:32.170546981Z","close_reason":"All 13 files SOUND across ~13,378 lines. Zero bugs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.334","title":"[audit][http] Make Limited body fail closed after terminal inner error","description":"src/http/body.rs currently only latches terminal completion for length-limit violations. If the inner body returns Some(Err(_)), Limited forwards the error but does not mark itself done, so a later poll can drive the failed inner body again. Scope: latch terminal failure and clean EOF locally in Limited so it never re-enters the inner body after a terminal result, add focused regression tests for both terminal inner error and EOF, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LilacLynx","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:05:19.165933356Z","created_by":"LilacLynx","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:59.546557817Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:52.810869450Z","close_reason":"Completed: src/http/body.rs Limited<B> now latches terminal state so post-error polls fail closed and post-EOF polls return None without re-entering the inner body; added focused regression tests for terminal inner error and EOF. Validation: rch exec -- cargo test --lib limited_body_ -- --nocapture passed; rch exec -- cargo fmt --check passed; rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets blocked by unrelated websocket test calls missing &Cx in tests/e2e/websocket/conformance/close.rs:29 and tests/e2e/websocket/integration/echo_server.rs:57; rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings blocked by unrelated existing lints in src/web/negotiate.rs:681 and src/transport/aggregator.rs:1268,1269,1324,1335.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.334","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:05:19.165933356Z","created_by":"LilacLynx"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.335","title":"[audit][web] Stop AsyncCxFnHandler wrappers from injecting test-only Cx","description":"src/web/handler.rs currently runs async web handlers on a hidden singleton runtime and injects a test-only Cx into every AsyncCxFnHandler wrapper. That bypasses real request and runtime ownership, deadlines, cancellation, and structured drain semantics promised by the adjacent request-region path. Scope: route async handler execution through a real request-owned runtime and context instead of the fabricated testing context, eliminate the sticky OnceLock Option Runtime outage mode if possible, and add focused regressions around request-scoped behavior.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CrimsonPeak","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:17:48.885826133Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:05:36.945587804Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0}

